Don't miss this!

Just like a visit to a 3-D movie! Animals almost jump into your lap. Wonderful 3-D stories for all ages!
name: Funny 3-D
Dragon Lady Presents Classic Adventure Strips

description:
1.  Efterlyst för Mord (Batman, James Gordon, Ra's al Ghul / written by Len Wein : translated from: Detective Comics #445)  
 
2.  Mord i Silver (Batman, James Gordon, Sterling Silversmith / written by Len Wein : translated from: Detective Comics #446)   
 
3. Odjur I Natten (Batman, Magic, Ivor / written by J. Marc DeMatteis : translated from: Detective Comics #489)
name: Efterlyst för Mord

description:
Doctor Doom confronts his master, the Marquis of Death! The Fantastic Four must battle a villain who has already killed them a thousand times across the mulitverse!

Also: classic action! Alicia Masters has been taken to the Beehive: a scientific wonderland housing a terrifying creature!

Includes material reprinted from Fantastic Four #567-568 and Fantastic Four (vol 1) #66.

Wolverine battles Victor Hudson, Romulus’s monstrous assassin! Daken becomes even more deadly, thanks to the Tinkerer! An old enemy resurfaces in Russia – Omega Red!

By Daniel Way and Doug Braithwaite.

Plus: Deadpool wants the Black Widow to be his new girlfriend – trouble is, she’s leading a team of mercenaries who want him dead!

By Daniel Way and Paco Medina.

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine: Origins #36-37 and Deadpool #9.

The race to find the new Sorcerer Supreme is on – and the Hood is in the lead! The Secret Avengers battle in New Orleans as the Eye of Agamotto makes its choice!

Also: Norman Osborn tries to hold the Dark Avengers together as the all-powerful Sentry becomes more unstable!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #5 and New Avengers #52-53.
name: Mystic War!

description:
Following immediately on the heels of 24/7, Spider-Man’s world has become more messed-up and stressful than ever and the fact that his biggest enemy, is in charge of the world…and the Avengers…is only the icing on a really dangerous cake.

Now faced with hard choices about family and friendship, Spider-Man knows exactly what he has to do to save the world…it’s time to take down Norman Osborn.

Spider-Man goes up against Venom and Bullseye as he prepares to infiltrate the Dark Avengers headquarters. Meanwhile Harry’s life takes a dramatic turn now that he’s reunited with Lily and wedding plans continue for two lucky Parker pals.

Also, classic adventure! New York is going crazy with flying sharks in the Midtown Tunnel, a deadly Spider-Man parade balloon, demons at the Empire State University and the return of the lethal Lizard! Spider-Man is up to his webs in trouble!

Story and art by Joe Kelly, Phil Jimenez, David Michelinie and Todd McFarlane!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #595-596 and Amazing Spider-Man #313! 76 pages! £2.95

The Mighty Avengers discover Norman Osborn’s new team – and they ain’t happy to see their name stolen! A trap is set, but who will be caught in it? Don’t miss an all-action epic!

Also: The Dark Avengers get their baptism of fire when they are forced to defend Doctor Doom against the world’s most powerful sorceress – Morgana Le Fey!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #50 and Dark Avengers #2.
name: The Dark Avengers Must Battle... The Hordes of Hellfire!

description:
Wolverine and Daken have joined forces and are on the hunt for the deadly Romulus! But before they can find him, they’ll have to face another obstacle: the monstrous Cyber!

By Daniel Way and Yanick Paquette.

Also: Deadpool chops San Diego into little pieces as he goes one-on-one with the lethal Tiger Shark!

By Daniel Way and Paco Medina.

Includes material reprinted from Wolverine: Origins #31-32 and Deadpool #6.

What is the Galactus Engine, and how will it rewrite human history?! The FF battle the New Defenders, and the Thing makes a dramatic decision that will change his life forever!

Also: classic thrills! There’s more action for the FF as the Sandman and Blastaar join forces!

Includes material reprinted from Fantastic Four #561-562 and Fantastic Four (vol 1) #63.
name: The Funeral of the Invisible Woman

description:
The Secret Invasion is over, and Norman Osborn is the winner! A chilling new era for the Marvel Universe begins as Osborn creates the Dark Avengers! Who are they? The answer will stun you! Can the Secret Avengers survive in a world that wants them dead? Find out here!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #1 and New Avengers #48-49
name: Who Are the Dark Avengers?

description:
When a bizarre criminal endangers his Aunt May, Peter Parker is determined to bring him to justice. But who is this strange, faceless felon? How can Spider-Man stop a guy who can slip through his webbing? And, hey, what's Pete’s pal Joe Robertson been up to?

Also, It would sure help Harry Osborn if he could remember the completely logical, non-magical, and totally plausible way he came back from the dead. A skill like that could be useful, now that his ex-brother-in-law, the Molten Man, is out to kill him! Set your spider-sense to tingling as some of the most requested secrets from the time between ‘One More Day’ and ‘Brand New Day’ are revealed. All this, and series regular, Liz Allen returns to the pages of Astonishing Spider-Man, but is she here to help her ex-husband, or to throw more fuel on the fire? And in answer to more requests than you would believe: Little Normie!

Plus, classic adventure! Everyone is after the Valencia Chalice, from the Black Fox, to the treacherous Transcorp and now, the Prowler! And guess who’s caught in the middle? Yep! Your friendly neighbourhood wall-crawler!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #580-581 and Amazing Spider-Man #305!
name: Secrets from Beyond the Grave!

description:
Random earthquakes don’t happen in New York. So how did one trap Spidey and a subway car full of New Yorkers underground? But there’s more to these passengers than meets the eye as a high-powered mob trial’s verdict is in their hands. And one of them has a crucial connection to Pete’s old boss, J. Jonah Jameson!

Plus, classic action, as Peter Parker has a book of his Spidey photos published! Well, more accurately J Jonah Jameson is, as he owns Pete’s photos lock (photo) stock and barrel! Fortunately, Pete is offered a chance to earn some big bucks from the book by going on tour to promote it. First stop, Los Angeles, where Peter discovers that the Black Fox is on the prowl!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #578-579 and Amazing Spider-Man #304!
name: Shock Tactics!

description:
Colossus encounters a horror from his childhood: the Tattooed Man! The Beast forms a new X-team! And in the wake of ‘ Secret Invasion’, the White Queen’s shocking past with the Sub-Mariner is revealed!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny X-Men #505 - Uncanny X-Men Annual #2 -Secret Invasion : Dark Reign #1
name: Secrets of the White Queen!

description:
A ‘Secret Invasion’ chapter! Hercules clashes with the Skrull god Kly’bn in a fight that will decide the survival of the cosmic pantheon – and if he loses, then Earth’s gods are doomed!

Also: Norman Osborn leads the Thunderbolts into the final battle against the Skrulls!

Includes material reprinted from Incredible Hercules #120 and Thunderbolts #124-125.
name: The Skrull God!

description:
The epic " Death of Captain America" tale hits its penultimate chapter and the final battle between the New Captain America and the people who killed Steve Rogers begins here!

Plus, an incredible new Iron Man adventure begins! Tony Stark – Iron Man, billionaire industrialist and director of S.H.I.E.L.D. – faces the most overwhelming challenge of his life. Ezekiel Stane, the son of Tony’s late business rival and archenemy Obadiah, has set his sights, his genius and his considerable fortune on the task of destroying Tony Stark and Iron Man. What’s worse, he’s got Iron Man tech, and he’s every bit Iron Man’s equal and opposite…except younger, faster, smarter…and immeasurably evil!

Also, as the Asgardians returned to this life and Thor returned to Midgard, so came the ills that have plagued the gods and man for millennia. Now for the first time since their rebirth, Thor and his fellow hero-gods are venturing forth from the Shining City to confront the growing evils that amass on their horizon…and within their walls…

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #41, Invincible Iron Man #1 and Thor #10!
name: Incredible NEW IRON MAN Saga Begins!

description:
The Molten Man's powers are out of control, setting the world ablaze around him, and destroying his own body and mind within. All he cares about is taking Harry Osborn with him! Can Spider-Man pull his best friend's fat out of this fire? And, with what Harry's been up to, should he? All this plus: a secret surprise from Liz Allan, and a major Spider-Mystery is finally solved. Also, after the revelations of “Mind on Fire”, love is in the air for more than one member of the cast and Pete finally gets some time out with the ladies. Amidst the romance though, forces are gathering that will spell trouble for Peter in the months to come.

Plus, classic adventure, as the web-slinger encounters the Humbug! Story and art by Dan Slott, Klaus Janson, Mark Waid, Zeb Wells, Barry Kitson, Todd Nauck, David Michelinie and Todd McFarlane!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #577 and Amazing Spider-Man #306!

76 pages!
name: Fists of Fury!

description:
The Beast, Angel and Dr Nemesis face the might of a monstrous creature in Japan – and they grow them BIG over there! Meanwhile, Colossus and Emma Frost take on the Tattooed Man!

Also: Charles Xavier confronts the man who hates him most of all – his step-brother, the unstoppable Juggernaut!

Includes material reprinted from Uncanny #506-507 and X-Men Legacy #219.
name: Colossus Cuts Loose!

description:
The Inhumans invade the Kree Empire, seeking vengeance on the Skrulls – and set in motion a conflict that will alter the Marvel Universe forever! ‘ War of Kings’ begins here!

Also: The Mighty Avengers are reborn! Earth succumbs to total chaos as the dark god Chthon returns! A new team of Avengers is needed: Hank Pym, Hercules, Iron Man, the Hulk, Amadeus Cho and USAgent join forces!

Plus: the classic origin of Black Bolt, and fact-files on the Mighty Avengers!

Includes material reprinted from Secret Invasion: War of Kings #1, Mighty Avengers #21 and Mighty Thor #149.
name: THE MIGHTY AVENGERS and THE INHUMANS

description: How does capturing and jailing super-criminals like The Joker impact the Gotham City Police Department — and how far will one officer go when faced with new threats to his city? Find out in this title collecting BATMAN CONFIDENTIAL #22-25 and 29-30!
name: TPB

description: Nightmares & Fairy Tales returns for a four issue series featuring the original creative team of Serena Valentino and FSc. Gwen and Annabelle venture off to find Morgan, a young woman who has been locked away in an asylum for many years for murders she did not commit. Soon, they find themselves in an abandoned town haunted by its own bloody past!
name: Part One

description: Dilton gets the perfect chance to test out the Wonder Realm, his new "immersive" gaming invention, when Archie's parents banish his gaming addiction to the basement! There's just one problem: once you get immersed in the game... how do you get out?!
name: Adventures in the Wonder Realm

description: A Night in the Comic Shop, Part Three. A visit to the Pep Comics Shop turns interdimensional! Jughead's cousin Souphead won't fall for Reggie's story about hordes of classic comic book characters unleashed on the town from a fallen meteorite... That is, until those legendary MLJ/Archie Comics characters return through interdimensional portals to prove it!
name: Return to the Comic Shop Part 1 of 2: Meteor Madness!

description: Near death from an attack by Slow Mutants, Roland Deschain is taken in by a group of Sisters who specialize in anything but the healing arts. These hideous, corpse-like creatures known as the Little Sisters of Eluria have murder on their twisted minds. And in his current, wounded condition, there's almost nothing the last gunslinger can do to prevent their tender mercies from taking hold. It's the beginning of a new Dark Tower story arc featuring the fine pencils of Luke Ross, whose work on this story will astound you! Don't miss it!
name: Issue 1 (of 5)

volume.name: The Dark Tower: The Gunslinger - The Little Sisters of Eluria

description:
WildStorm's most enigmatic team returns in this special edition collecting two stories fans won't want to miss!

First, during an investigation of The Authority, the post-human pantheon intrudes in one of Planetary's old cases. Then we introduce the new Planetary field crew – Clark Kent, Bruce Wayne and Diana Prince? The WildStorm Universe's mystery-tackling team collides with the DC Universe's Greatest Heroes in the most unexpected way! Featuring art by Phil Jimenez (INFINITE CRISIS, Amazing Spider-Man) and Jerry Ordway and written by superstar Warren Ellis (AUTHORITY, TRANSMETROPOLITAN)!
name: 100-Page Spectacular

description: The shattering conclusion to the 6-issue miniseries is here as Sheriff Lindo makes one last, desperate gamble to stop Derek Fury. But will it be enough? Will even a town full of super humans have the strength to overcome one foe fueled by unbelievable hatred and rage?
name: Homecoming part six: Ending Note

volume.name: Welcome to Tranquility: One Foot in the Grave

description: It's Scooby and Shaggy's dream come true: they've got the run of a bakery! Unfortunately, their sweet paradise is haunted. This is one mystery they're hungry to solve!
name: The Ghost of Christmas Presents; The Truth

description: The Bat Man, Doc Savage and The Spirit are all on the scene in Hidalgo uncovering the secrets of Anton Colossi and his floating city. But Colossi still has a secret weapon that could put them all in their graves…along with nearly everyone else on Earth!
name: First Wave - Book 5

description: Kestrel, the mad dog of the Chaos Realm, battles the Teen Titans in a bid to gain power like he's never had before in a tale from TEEN TITANS #27-28. And in an epic from LEGENDS OF THE DC UNIVERSE #26-27, The Joker earns the wrath of both Aquaman and Batman when he dredges up the old Joker-fish routine.
name: DC Comics Presents: Brightest Day 100-Page Spectacular #3

description: It's Tom & Jerry meets 28 Days Later as the Littlest Zombie and the Littlest Vampire fight tooth and nail, hand-to-detachable-hand for scant sustenance! Their quarry, the Littlest Survivor, must pull out every trick in the Apocalypse Survivor's Handbook to keep his two supernatural stalkers at each other's throats and off his!
name: One Shot

volume.name: The Littlest Zombie vs The Littlest Vampire

description:
Having made her decision to come back into hero work, Dynagirl sets out in search of some help, but putting a new team together isn't as easy as she thought!

Five years after the tragic end of Fallen Justice we find Kerri Masters struggling in more ways than one with the events of the past. She has retired, and seemingly moved on from her former life as one of the world’s premier heroes. But when she meets a mysterious woman who offers her the chance to return to her glory days as the costumed heroine Dynagirl, she must finally come face to face with the ghosts that seem to haunt her wherever she goes.

A teenager with incredible speed powers shows up and is scouring the world in search of Kerri Masters, the alter ego of Dynagirl! Meanwhile, Kerri and her newly formed team are confronted with an ever growing and potentially catastrophic storm bearing down on the East coast of the United States. The storm is anything but natural, and it may well have dangerous ties to Dynagirl's past.

She has retired, and seemingly moved on from her former life as one of the world’s premier heroes. But when she meets a mysterious woman who offers her the chance to return to her glory days as the costumed heroine Dynagirl, she must finally come face to face with the ghosts that seem to haunt her wherever she goes.

Overview:

In this tale of misperceptions and mistaken identities, the Man of Steel and the super-powered teens of Gen 13 team up in a humorous and action packed-adventure. While witnessing a titanic battle between Superman and a cyborg gorilla, Fairchild heroically stands in to lessen the impact of the Man of Steel against a cement wall. Grateful that he has not harmed the unknown good samaritan, Superman wraps Fairchild in his cape and returns to battle. But when the now amnesiac Fairchild assumes that she is Supergirl, it is up to the rest of Gen13 and Superman to save the city and Fairchild from herself.
name: Superman/Gen 13
